es, such as admissions, financial aid, instruction and assessment, retention and graduation, student life, diversity, finances, athletics, governance, and marketing. This book is essential reading for educators and laypeople who are interested in learning how our universities work and how they could work better.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, HighervMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aEducation, HigherxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aEducation, HigherxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited States. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aPhilosophy & Religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170631840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501706318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501706318/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles